The Soviet martial art of SAMBO and modern MMA can be put in the same categories as Esperanto, McDonald's fast food, the forceful cultural destruction of the Eurasian peoples by the Soviets, and universalism.

Inherently utilitarian, material, artificial, and atheistic - STERILE!

A sad reality of MMA is that it is castrated of all symbolic meaning and spirituality.

Traditional folk wrestling forms and natural martial arts are more than a set of rules and fighting moves. They carry a specific worldview and an esoteric aspect, which is missing in MMA.

Rene Guenon (and @clavemscientiae) would call this a falling away from the divinity, which is typical for the Kali Yuga. The true meaning is lost, and the essence of the practice is replaced with a simple vulgar fight. All substance is lost and now the sole goal is "winning".

This is another reason why we see MMA prevail today. It is inherently artificial and vain, there is no true depth to it as there is in aikido, sumo, pehlivan fighting etc. 

What used to hold meaning is reduced now to a simple sport, with goal no greater than winning the match.

As your body progresses and you hone your skills, you are not moving spiritually, you remain in stagnation. This is not natural, this is not how it is meant to be.

As one "sceptic" (I spit upon him) said:

"sambo doesn't demand any sort of transformative "journey" from you"
